HEADWORD: judgmental
<hw>judgmental</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>depending on
judgment; <as>as, a <ex>judgmental</ex> error</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Inclined to make moral judgements about the behavior
of people; -- contrasted with an inclination not to judge the moral
qualities of others. Opposite of <ant>nonjudgmental</ant>.</def>
[Narrower terms: <stype>faultfinding(prenominal) </stype>]⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>judgship</ent>⟦br⟧
